Steps to run:

*****************************************************************************
1) Please run make file from the code directory using this command to compile all the files submitted for the Homework 1:
	cd 32_010466651_HW1
	32_010466651_HW1>make 
*****************************************************************************	
2) For question 1, please run this command to see the output:
	cd 32_010466651_HW1
	32_010466651_HW1> sudo ./processThreads 

*****************************************************************************	
3) For question 2, please run this command to see the output:
	cd 32_010466651_HW1
	32_010466651_HW1> sudo ./execvExecution 

3) For question 4 in client and server models, please run below commands to see out put
	a. TCP-based server/client:
		cd 32_010466651_HW1
		32_010466651_HW1> sudo ./TCPServer  12003
Open another terminal window for the client:
		cd 32_010466651_HW1
		32_010466651_HW1> sudo ./TCPClient  localhost 12003
Now observe the messages passed between two terminals. 
	
b. UDP-based server/client:
		cd 32_010466651_HW1
		32_010466651_HW1> sudo ./UDPServer  12005
Open another terminal window for the client:
		cd 32_010466651_HW1
		32_010466651_HW1> sudo ./UDPClient  localhost 12005
Now observe the messages passed between two terminals.  After Observing, the Server is still running in this case as I have included a while loop. You can stop the server using “control c”  command.

*****************************************************************************	
